        <dc:subject>
           <z:AutomaticTag><rdf:value>/unread</rdf:value></z:AutomaticTag>
        </dc:subject>
        <dc:title>Reliable collision avoidance for small UAVs via deep reinforcement learning with unified data representation</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>Collision avoidance is a fundamental capability for multi-UAV systems to complete autonomous tasks. For small rotary-wing UAVs, due to their limited perception capacities and flight endurance, achieving reliable collision avoidance remains challenging. To this end, we propose a reliable multi-UAV collision avoidance method based on deep reinforcement learning, which leverages information from neighboring UAVs to augment the onboard perception capabilities. This method utilizes a technique called unified data representation (UDR) to combine depth data from LiDAR measurements and information from neighboring UAVs into a compact feature embedding, which can effectively integrate various observations with significant dimensional differences and inconsistent environmental expressions. Based on this, the collision avoidance policy hosted by a neural network is learned and produces control references for each UAV to ensure safety during flight. The training experiments demonstrate that our method achieves approximately a 20% improvement in average rewards compared to baseline approaches, using the same number of training episodes. Additionally, we perform validation experiments using the PX4 flight controller in a soft-in-the-loop (SITL) setup within the Gazebo simulator. Experimental results show that our approach significantly improves the reliability of collision avoidance, particularly in scenarios involving inter-aircraft collisions.</dcterms:abstract>
        <dc:date>2025-07-09</dc:date>
        <z:language>en</z:language>
        <z:libraryCatalog>DOI.org (Crossref)</z:libraryCatalog>
        <dc:identifier>
            <dcterms:URI>
                <rdf:value>https://www.worldscientific.com/doi/10.1142/S2301385026500500</rdf:value>
            </dcterms:URI>
        </dc:identifier>
        <dcterms:dateSubmitted>2026-07-22 08:33:10</dcterms:dateSubmitted>
        <bib:pages>1-12</bib:pages>
    </bib:Article>
